cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper uses automated language analysis to identify mental disorders, specifically schizophrenia and bipolar disorder. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to train a classifier, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on the assessment of social skills, which could potentially fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
